description.plain:
On “Die Today,” producer Cassius Jay enlists the help of Lil Uzi Vert for a track where Uzi declares the completion of his life goals.

The track was recorded in 2017 during production of Uzi’s album Luv Is Rage 2 and was thrown away from the project. It was previewed by Uzi in April 2017 at a show and on Instagram. It was released by Cassius on August 9, 2019. It was removed from streaming services and YouTube on August 15, 2019, supposedly because Cassius used its artwork without permission, and was not rereleased.

description.plain:
On “Big Racks,” producer Cassius Jay enlists the help of Philadelphia rapper Lil Uzi Vert for a braggadocios banger. On the track, Uzi explores his exorbitant wealth and reflects on the lavish lifestyle he lives, while also reaffirming his commitment to making more money. Uzi’s net worth is approximately $3 million.

This track marks the first collaboration between Lil Uzi Vert and the producer Cassius Jay.

description.plain:
“Hard For Me” features an autotune-drenched Takeoff contrasting his struggles growing up and his current success over a smooth beat produced by frequent Migos collaborators Cassius Jay and Murda Beatz.

The song notably shares its instrumental with “Testarossa” by A$AP Ant featuring Hoodrich Pablo Juan and, humorously enough, fellow Migo Offset.

The track leaked on unreleased music forum leakth.is on May 21st, 2019. However, it didn’t see a commercial release until Jay placed it on his third studio album Trap Sinatra 2 more than a year later, on June 30th, 2020.
